                            <comment id="17442354" author="psteitz" created="Thu, 11 Nov 2021 16:54:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A fix for this is in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-pool/pull/113&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-pool/pull/113&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The lack of &quot;atomicity&quot; is by design, to avoid synchronization delays waiting for creates to complete.&#160; Other public methods that create capacity (return, invalidate, evict, etc) call reuseCapacity, which allocates freed capacity to pools that have borrowers waiting.&#160; The PR modifies clear() to (optionally) do this.&#160;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
